dcterms:description: The General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) is one of the most influential pieces of European Union (EU) legislation in the last decade, changing business practices within the EU and causing a 'Brussels Effect' abroad.
dcterms:title: GDPR (General Data Protection Regulation)

dcterms:description: The proposed AI Act aims to introduce new standards and conformity assessment requirements for 'high-risk' AI products sold in the EU, potentially influencing global AI regulation.
dcterms:title: AI Act (Artificial Intelligence Act)

dcterms:description: The CE Marking is a certification mark that indicates conformity with health, safety, and environmental protection standards for products sold within the European Economic Area.
dcterms:title: CE Marking

dcterms:description: REACH is a European Union regulation that addresses the production and use of chemical substances and their potential impacts on human health and the environment.
dcterms:title: REACH (Registration, Evaluation, Authorisation and Restriction of Chemicals)

dcterms:description: The AI White Paper outlines the European Commission's approach to artificial intelligence, emphasizing the need for a regulatory framework that fosters innovation while ensuring safety and ethical standards.
dcterms:title: AI White Paper
